The paper deals with document retrieval for content analysis, which is a task commonly associated with information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Topic Models, which are a popular machine learning technique used in various sub-fields of computer science, including cs.LG and cs.DL. Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method, which is a common theme in the sub-field of information retrieval evaluation, which falls under cs.SI.
